'''Force Burst''' was a [[Force power/Legends|Force power]] that could be used by a [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] or [[Sith/Legends|Sith]]. The strength of the Burst depended on the amount of time and energy put into it.

A Burst's size and intensity could range anywhere from huge and combustible, to small, but relatively deadly. It was usually semi-transparent with a blue or green hue, where as the Sith variant had a reddish shade. The sphere of [[Force energy]] sought out its intended target with the utmost accuracy and speed. This technique could be nullified by [[Tutaminis|Force protection]], [[Protection bubble]], or set off course by a strong [[Telekinesis/Legends|Force push]], or even dissipated with another Force Burst. However, it was usually deflected by a well-timed [[Force barrier/Legends|Force shield]]. A similar, far more harmful dark-side Force ability is known as [[Force Destruction]], where the user would unleash a Force energy using their body as a conduit.

{{Force-stub}}

==Behind the scenes==
[[Qui-Gon Jinn/Legends|Qui-Gon Jinn]] and [[Obi-Wan Kenobi/Legends|Obi-Wan Kenobi]] used this technique in the [[Wikipedia:PlayStation (console)|PlayStation]] game, ''Star Wars Episode I: Jedi Power Battles''.

